article.headline: Tigers break open game with 18-4 run
article.linkText: Augustus leads No. 1 LSU easily over Santa Barbara
article.story:
SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (Ticker) -- Seimone Augustus led four 
players in double figures with 16 points as No. 1 LSU continued
its unbeaten start with a 72-52 victory over Santa Barbara on Tuesday night.

Augustus shot 6-of-12 from the field and Temeka Johnson added 11
points and seven assists for the Lady Tigers (11-0), who opened
up a 14-12 game with an 18-4 run and led 36-25 at the half.

Scholanda Hoston scored 16 points and Quianna Chaney chipped in
11 for LSU, which limited the Gauchos (2-4) to 36 percent
(19-of-53) shooting en route to holding its seventh opponent in
its last eight games below 55 points.

Kristen Mann had 22 points and seven rebounds for Santa Barbara,
which committed 23 turnovers.
